pr_review_body:
@jjyao code looks good, but one issue I noticed is that we don't log anything when retrying these exceptions (you at least get some warning for retried system-level errors).

How about adding a message that we're retrying with `CoreWorker::PushError`?

(btw, this is kind of related to a tech debt item where RAY_LOG(ERROR) doesn't show in console for core worker logs, but that's a bit bigger to fix: https://github.com/ray-project/ray/issues/12893)

@mulhod thank you, this looks really good!

I just had a few minor comments. If you can fix those up we'll get this merged 🎉 

As a side note, I feel like the `overrides` argument throughout the library should accept a JSON string or a Python dictionary. That would make it much easier to use from Python directly. What do you think?

@fukatani it would also be cool to update the doc string of the `predict` method a lil bit:
https://github.com/apple/coremltools/blob/main/coremltools/models/model.py#L468
Maybe include a simple example that make the prediction with torch / tf tensor

@Br4nd0R The fix I had in mind for this was to indent the "if delete_org:" block so that it is inside the "finally:" block and will run even if the flow raised an exception.

I don't think we want to suppress the raising of the exception. That will prevent the stacktrace from being captured in the cci log.

And I don't think we need to explicitly log the exception here. That is already done within the flowrunner.

Nice; thanks! Only request is to remove nPMI special-casing if we can;
if that doesn’t work for some reason, happy to keep it. (I do want to
support it; I just think that we might get it for free.)

```
try:
       self.rollback()
   except:
       raise
   else:
       raise MergeConfigException(merge_error)

``` 
Like this ?

@karczex, thank you for the PR!

Is it enough for you to have `pkg-config` support for build from sources only? Are you interested in having it in prebuilt packages from [release](https://github.com/oneapi-src/oneTBB/releases) page (not sure how to dynamically get `prefix` value in this case)?

Overall comment: the PR covers only `tbb` library in release configuration, but we need to take into account other oneTBB libraries (tbbmalloc, tbbbind, etc), consider debug libraries that have `_debug` suffix (`-ltbb_debug`). Most likely we should implement a common macro to run it for each target.

@busunkim96 @anguillanneuf  Took another look, plenty of autogenerated stuff, but seems good.

I also see why several entries refer to the same commit, it's simply because that commit was so large.

Please have a look at the suggested changes in CHANGELOG, but otherwise I think we can release this today.

LGTM, thank you @oke-aditya for your contribution and for your patience. :) 

I checked the modes and they look fine to me.

@pmeier Do you mind also having a look that we are good to go? Once I get your stamp we can merge.
